The paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics, specifically the Clique-Stable Set separation problem in a subclass of perfect graphs. This problem is related to graph decomposition and coloring algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), followed by cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves some graph theoretic concepts such as the Strong Perfect Graph Theorem and the Erd?s-Hajnal property, which may place it in the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) category. Finally, the paper presents a generalized k-join operation, which could potentially fit in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) category.
